# 1. Single Responsibility Principle (SRP)

## Definition

A class should have only one responsibility and one reason to change.

### Benefits

* Better readability
* Easier maintenance
* Low coupling
* Better testing

---

## ❌ Violation

```java
class Employee {

    private String name;
    private double salary;

    public Employee(String name, double salary) {
        this.name = name;
        this.salary = salary;
    }

    public void calculateSalary() {
        System.out.println("Salary: " + salary);
    }

    public void saveToDatabase() {
        System.out.println("Employee saved to DB");
    }
}
```

### Problem

Employee class handles:

* Employee data
* Salary calculation
* Database operations

Multiple responsibilities violate SRP.

---

## ✅ Correct Implementation

```java
class Employee {

    private String name;
    private double salary;

    public Employee(String name, double salary) {
        this.name = name;
        this.salary = salary;
    }

    public double getSalary() {
        return salary;
    }
}

class SalaryCalculator {

    public void calculate(Employee emp) {
        System.out.println("Salary: " + emp.getSalary());
    }
}

class EmployeeRepository {

    public void save(Employee emp) {
        System.out.println("Employee saved to DB");
    }
}
```

### Structure

```text
Employee
   │
   ├── SalaryCalculator
   │
   └── EmployeeRepository
```

